    InfiniteArrays.Infinity — Type.

    Infinity()

    represents infinite cardinality. Note that Infinity <: Integer to support being treated as an index.

    InfiniteArrays.OneToInf — Type.
    OneToInf(n)

    Define an AbstractInfUnitRange that behaves like 1:∞, with the added distinction that the limits are guaranteed (by the type system) to be 1 and ∞.
